      "writtenOn": "2026-06-15T08:38:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I am wondering if it makes sense to create a whole new service, executable and process here.\n\nFrom what i read so far we are creating a single match from `main()` function, and not much else happens unless that match triggers.\n\nIf we just integrated the whole thing into an existing binary, there could be savings in overall compressed rofs size.\n\nIMO conceptually it would fit into the FruDevice binary. Then we could just select which one to run based on a commandline argument.\n\nNow if we should make it a separate process, that\u0027s another question, i do not think so. But others may have a different opinion.",
      "revId": "5128a93978aa0cadc4d2af8e5d24b99962054de5",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9895d422_df33ae1f",
        "filename": "service_files/nfc-fru-parser.service",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002728
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-16T09:12:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The main reason I separated it was to keep the functionality isolated from FruDevice and make the code easier to maintain. However, I understand the concern about adding another service and configuration option for a lightweight feature. I can look into implementing it within FruDevice if that better aligns with the project\u0027s direction.\nThanks.",
      "parentUuid": "d8ed81a3_746b2085",
      "revId": "5128a93978aa0cadc4d2af8e5d24b99962054de5",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
